Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Cook penne rigate according to package directions. Meanwhile, in large skillet, brown ground beef with onions; drain. Reduce heat to medium-low; add chiles, mushrooms, stewed tomatoes and marinara. Cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Spray 9x13-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Add cooked pasta. Pour meat sauce over pasta. Sprinkle with cheeses. Bake 15 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.